      {
        "caption": "<strong>Step 2.</strong> Forward transfers show the dependency flow as it actually runs. Below the diagonal, each mark is a direct invocation or load.",
        "reveal": {
          "include": [
            "diagonal",
            "transfer:directed:forward"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "caption": "<strong>Step 3.</strong> No backward transfers above the diagonal — the rendered dependencies sort cleanly into layers, so ordinary topological sorting succeeds.",
        "reveal": {
          "include": [
            "diagonal",
            "transfer:directed:forward",
            "transfer:directed:backward"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "caption": "<strong>Step 4.</strong> No backward transfers and no cyclic core — the system is fully hierarchical, so it sorts into dependency layers rather than a core-periphery partition.<br/><em>Architecture: hierarchical.</em>",
        "reveal": {
          "include": [
            "diagonal",
            "transfer:directed:forward",
            "transfer:directed:backward"
          ]
        }
